## Quick start

```bash
./dev               # install uv + just, sync deps, install lefthook
just docs::live     # live-reload preview at http://localhost:8000
```

## Common commands

```bash
just docs::live        # local live-reload preview
just docs::build       # build static site into site/
just docs::validate    # lint (markdown/spelling) + clean build
just docs::image-run   # serve the built site via nginx at http://localhost:8080
just version::bump patch && just version::tag   # cut a release tag
```

## Updating from the template

```bash
just copier::update   # pull the latest copier-docs changes (commit your work first)
```

## CI/CD

{% if ci_platform == 'gitlab' -%}
The docs pipeline is isolated in **`ci/docs.gitlab-ci.yml`** (the root
`.gitlab-ci.yml` just `include:`s it, so it drops into a mixed repo cleanly).
Jobs are `docs`-namespaced and call `just docs::*`: `docs-lint` + `docs-build`
on push/MR, **GitLab Pages** on `{{ '$CI_DEFAULT_BRANCH' }}`, and
**`docs-release-image`** — a versioned nginx image pushed to
`{{ gitlab_registry }}:<tag>` + `:latest` — only on `vX.Y.Z` tags.
{%- else -%}
Three isolated workflows under `.github/workflows/`: **`docs.yml`** (lint + build
on push/PR), **`docs-pages.yml`** (deploy to **GitHub Pages** on the default
branch), and **`docs-release.yml`** — a versioned nginx image pushed to
`{{ github_registry }}:<tag>` + `:latest` — only on `vX.Y.Z` tags. They call
`just docs::*`.
{%- endif %}

Cut a release image by tagging: `just version::bump patch && just version::tag`.

## Editing the docs

All content is Markdown under `docs/`. Add new pages to the `nav` table in
`zensical.toml`. The [Showcase](docs/showcase.md) page demonstrates the available
formatting (admonitions, code highlighting, content tabs, card grids, diagrams,
and Markdown includes).
